// golden_set.jsonl — RAG evaluation golden set
//
// Format: one JSON object per line. Lines starting with // or # are skipped.
// Schema mirrors app/test/eval/schema.py:GoldenSample. Field reference:
//
//   qid                    — unique short id, e.g. "sv-001" (single_video #1)
//   category               — single_video | cross_video | negation |
//                            proper_noun | numeric_fact | abstract
//   question               — the question to ask the RAG pipeline
//   scope                  — vector | direct | db_list | db_content
//   folder_ids             — bilibili favorite folder ids (optional)
//   must_contain_bvid      — at least one of these BVs must appear in top-K
//                            (drives recall@5; required for vector scope when
//                            must_contain_keywords is empty)
//   must_contain_keywords  — strings that should appear in the final answer
//                            (case-insensitive substring match)
//   expected_answer_points — natural-language facts the answer should cover
//                            (consumed by the LLM judge, NOT for substring
//                            matching)
//   negative_keywords      — strings that MUST NOT appear in the answer;
//                            any hit caps answer_quality at 1
//   min_chunks             — minimum chunks expected (currently informational)
//   tags                   — free-form labels for slicing reports
//   created_at             — ISO date (optional)
//   owner                  — who curated this row
//
// ── Domain note (2026-06-14) ───────────────────────────────────
// Current vector store contains only one core CS-foundations video:
//   BV1qG41197E4  "计算机组成原理微课堂"  (5 pages: 课程介绍 / 系统组成 /
//                  计算机的发展 / 计算机硬件 / 计算机软件)
// All seed rows below probe that single video. Because there is only
// one BV, cross_video is simulated as a question that needs facts
// from TWO different pages of the same video; recall@5 will be
// near-saturated (everything matches BV1qG41197E4), so MRR@5 is the
// primary signal for the rerank A/B comparison.
// When more videos are vectorized, replace these rows with real
// multi-BV cross_video questions.
//
// Validation runs automatically on load (see schema.validate_golden_set).
// Common errors: duplicate qid, vector scope with no anchors, missing fields.

